"{\n  \"text\": \"In the past five to ten years, a lot of research has uncovered the functions of gut bacteria. It's not just about digesting your food and knocking out the pathogenic bacteria that's on your food. It's also in charge of running a lot of your organ functions. At first it was thought that it was just the brain and this and that. That because so many of your brain's neurochemicals are created in your gut, they figure there must be some link and they found it. It's a vargas nerve. And what they're also finding out now is that it's not just your brain, it's all of your organ functions are regulated by your gut bacteria. It's the command center for your bodily functions. This is why it's so important to cultivate healthy bacteria because it's not just about digestion, it's about organ function, all of your organs, particularly your brain though. This is something that's so crucial because a lot of us are suffering with a lot of different anxiety, a lot of different depression. A lot of this has to do with the neurochemicals that are created from your gut bacteria. Eat more fermented foods, it's good for you.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" In the past five to ten years, a lot of research has uncovered the functions of gut bacteria.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 5.52,\n      \"duration\": 5.2,\n      \"confidence\": 0.995,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" In\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.985\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" the\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" past\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.88,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" f\",\n          \"start\": 0.88,\n          \"